### Test Authentication Endpoints
### Use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api
@token = your-jwt-token-here

### 1. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "test.user",
  "password": "Esnad123456789"
}

### 2. Get Profile (requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Change Password (requires token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/change-password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "currentPassword": "Esnad123456789",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword123"
}

### 4. Refresh Token (requires token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh-token
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Test Protected Route - Get Users (requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Test Role-based Access (example)
# This would require implementing role protection on specific routes
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}